# fleet wiring rule

Use `signalos fleet` to operate the governed agent fleet runtime. SignalOS
enforces, never advises: every agent hand-off passes a governance admission
check and fails closed without an active wave/gate or a valid agent packet.

- Use `signalos fleet detect` to discover which agent CLIs (claude-code, codex,
  cursor, github-copilot, windsurf, gemini, and others) are installed; it
  writes runtime evidence to `.signalos/evidence/fleet/runtimes.json`.
- Use `signalos fleet list` to inspect the detected runtime records.
- Use `signalos fleet gc` to TTL-prune isolated task workspaces under
  `.signalos/fleet/tasks/`. It removes done/idle and orphaned task dirs, prunes
  heavy artifact dirs (`node_modules`, `.next`, `.turbo`) while preserving
  source, `.git`, and `logs`, and writes a `fleet-gc` audit row.
- Do not dispatch an agent outside the governed admission path; a dispatch
  without an active wave/gate or a valid agent packet is refused and audited,
  never silently allowed.
- The live server-backed executor is roadmap; see
  `docs/GOVERNED_FLEET_RUNTIME_DESIGN.md` for what is foundation vs roadmap.
